gh hermeneutics and semiotics up to the present state of self-annihilation. As an alternative, the book seeks to define humanities as the examination of relationships, which offers an array of refreshing perspectives on each field discussed.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aDialogism (Literary analysis). 0aHumanitiesxResearch. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Comparative Literature.2bisacsh  aBakhtin dialogics.  adialogic interculturality.  adialogic post-modernity.  adialogical design.  adialogical philosophy.  adialogical psychology.  adialogical sociology.  adialogicity of epochs.  aefforts to unite the humanities.  ahistory of ideas.1 aAndrianova, Maria, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBoháček, Kryštof, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFreise, Matthias, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKaczmarczyk, Michal, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKrippendorff, Klaus, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPlassmann, Reinhard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWang, Xiaojing, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAcademic Studies Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311068818440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978161811739740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781618117397423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781618117397/original  a978-3-11-068818-4  Academic Studies Press Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5E